

### SPATIAL QUANTIFICATION AND PLOTTING


# For EACH sample:
# 
# Detect physical boundary (COMâ€“TRA)
#
# Compute:
# slope (developmental speed)
# variability (temporal heterogeneity)
# activity (speed Ã— heterogeneity)
#
# Smooth fields using Thin Plate Spline
#
# Compute âˆ‡(activity) --> dynamic front
#
# Label dynamic boundary
#
# compute front sharpness (grad mag)
# compute divergence
# compute Moran's Index for spatial autocorrelation of front cells
# Attach region + boundary info
# 
# Then:
# Combine all samples
# Compute % dynamic boundary per region per group
# Ready for plotting/statistics



